		<outline text="June 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="june2021" >
			<outline text="June 25" type="calendarDay" name="25" >
				<outline text="Playing Spatial Audio off of an M1-based Apple Mac sounds way better than using the latest Apple TV.

Here is the kicker: this is true of you Airplay to that same Apple TV.

If you want the best sound you have to play around." type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 16:07:21 GMT" tweetId="1408456790983905281" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1408456790983905281" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				<outline text="Did you know billionaires have 12K screens and pay up to $500 to watch a cinema-release of a movie? (One I was talking to has a theater in their new home. A bunch called about my lights).

Next year Apple’s “Holodeck” (my made-up name for its VR headset) will be way better. https://t.co/AVDJsEFo3l" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 10:31:19 GMT" tweetId="1408372225569263618" urltweet="https://twitter.com/scobleizer/status/1408372225569263618" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="scobleizer" />
				</outline>
			</outline>
